  "prompt": "What are some of the best ways to buy PC games at a low rate?",
  "response": "Buying PC games at a low rate can involve various strategies, and here are some of the best ways to do so:\n\n1. **Steam Sales:** Steam is known for its frequent sales events, such as the Summer Sale, Winter Sale, and Black Friday Sale. During these times, games can be heavily discounted.\n\n2. **Humble Bundle:** Humble Bundle offers bundles of games at a \"pay-what-you-want\" price, with a portion of the proceeds going to charity. They often provide great value for money with substantial discounts on high-quality titles.\n\n3. **Epic Games Store Free Games:** The Epic Games Store regularly gives away free games, sometimes even AAA titles. Keep an eye on their weekly free game offerings.\n\n4. **GOG.com (Good Old Games):** GOG.com offers DRM-free games and has frequent sales. Their selection includes both modern and classic titles, often at reduced prices.\n\n5. **Fanatical:** Fanatical is another platform that offers bundles and discounts on PC games. They often have sales events featuring significant markdowns.\n\n6. **Comparative Websites:** Use websites like IsThereAnyDeal, GG.deals, or CheapShark to compare prices across various digital distribution platforms to find the best deals available.\n\n7. **Retailer Coupons and Promotions:** Some retailers and digital platforms offer occasional coupons, discounts, and promotional codes. Sign up for newsletters or follow social media accounts to stay updated on these deals.\n\n8. **Subscription Services:** Services like Xbox Game Pass for PC provide access to a large library of games for a monthly fee. This can be highly cost-effective if you frequently play new games.\n\n9. **Community Marketplaces:** Websites like Reddit (r/GameDeals) or forums often share information about the latest deals. Community-driven marketplaces sometimes also offer cheaper prices due to lower overheads.\n\n10. **Patience:** Waiting for a game to go on sale or for a price drop can save you money. Prices for games typically decrease after release, especially during major sales events.\n\nBy combining these strategies, you can maximize your savings on PC games and expand your gaming library without breaking the bank.",
